**Change Log:**  
**Playtest**  
0.0.1: Health for each player lowered to 5  
0.0.2: Healing adjusted to go after damage  
0.0.3: Cards labeled Gain or Loss to help with clarity in signifying what the card is supposed to do  
**Physical Prototype**  
0.0.4: Healing nerfed so games don’t stale. The Fool now heals 1 regardless of target, and the Fool’s old effect is given to the Queen  
0.0.5: Some Player Cards only have 5 copies of them because they are really good or obnoxious, making them rarer to come up in play  
**Digital Prototype**  
0.0.6: Cards only labeled gain/loss in instructions to make cards easier to read  
0.0.7: Game now themed around fortune, card art made to mimic Tarot Cards  
0.0.8: Game name changed from Pit Maneuvers to Fools  
0.0.9: Pit Deck and Pit changed to Center Deck and Center to fit new thematic  
0.0.10: Card art changed to fit thematic (this hurt me)

**Fools Instructions:**

1. **Setup**  
   1. **Preparations:**  
      1. **Disclaimer:** There are 2 decks that are in play, the Center Deck and the Player Deck. The Pit deck holds all Jesters, all Fools, and one Executioner card while the Player Deck holds every other card.  
      2. **Center Setup:** Take 3 Fools and 3 Jesters from the Center Deck and place them face down in a line between both players. That line with the cards just placed in it is the Center. Then, shuffle the Center Deck and the Player Deck and each player will draw 4 cards from the player deck.   
      3. **Card Setup:** Once both players have picked up their 4 cards, choose 2 and place them face down in the Center. Once both players have played their cards, shuffle the Center so neither player knows which card is which and the game has started.   
2. **Battle Phase**  
   1. **Pick Phase:** 1 player counts down from 3 (eg:  “On GO: 3, 2, 1, GO”) and each player picks a card by placing their hand on it. Then players will push the card into the direction of the player they want to play the card on (towards themselves or towards the opponent). Once both players pick their card the Turn Phase starts.  
      1. **Contested:** If both players choose the same card, flip a coin to see who gets the card.  
   2. **Turn Phase:** Each player turns their card and plays its effect to the player it was played on.  
3. **Card Phase**  
   1. Every 2 turns (or whenever there are 6 cards in the pit) pick the top 2 cards from the Center Deck and players play 1 card in their hand. Shuffle the Center and draw 1 card from the Player Deck.   
4. **Winning/Losing/Goals**  
   1. Each player has 5 health, there are cards that heal and cards that do damage as well as some miscellaneous cards that can help or hurt players. The goal is to get your opponent to 0 health. If both players go to 0 health at the same time, it’s a tie (or flip a coin to determine the winner if agreed upon).
